      {
        "heading": "S",
        "section_value": "The patient reports intermittent back pain, primarily on the left, which is sometimes sharp and sometimes not, and occasionally moves. He also reports increased urine output, particularly at night, and unchanged appetite. He denies recent illness or fever. He reports that school is going well and mentions his physics teacher's socks. He notes that everyone seems to be sick these days. He has a brother who smokes and has been told not to smoke, but does not listen. He has a history of recurrent strep infections, having experienced four in the last five months.",
