      },
      {
        "heading": "A",
        "section_value": "The patient's symptoms, particularly the recurrent strep infections and left back pain, raise concern for potential glomerular nephritis. A referral to an ENT is warranted to evaluate the possibility of tonsillectomy. Further investigations, including a CT scan and laboratory testing, are needed to assess the extent of the glomerular nephritis and rule out other causes of the symptoms.",
        "medical_concepts": [
          "recurrent strep infections",
          "left back pain",
          "glomerular nephritis",
          "ENT referral",
          "tonsillectomy",
          "CT scan",
          "laboratory testing"
        ]
      },
      {
        "heading": "P",
        "section_value": "I am ordering a lipid panel, a UA, a CMP, a CBC, a vitamin D, and a TSH. I am referring the patient to an ENT for evaluation and consideration of tonsillectomy. I will schedule a follow-up appointment in one week to review the results and discuss further management strategies. I will also counsel the patient's brother on the importance of avoiding smoking and encourage him to seek support if needed.",
